V.3





TO: VICTOR REYNOLDS1

CC, 1 p.

Ithaca, N.Y.





September 7, 1958

Dear Mr. Reynolds,

I cannot conceal my disappointment at not getting any royalty from your edition of my "Onegin". However, I do understand your reluctance to pay royalties since you expect to sell only 975 copies over a period of several years. I have a hunch that it will sell much better than that. Let us say, the